reviews.review_text:
Music Worth Driving Hours For Drove down from Charlotte NC for the 1st of a 4 show run. Manor Downs was wide open. No security hassles. 
I did some shrooms but didn’t think they were kicking in so I dropped a hit of acid. Then the sheooms kicked in! Man I was flying for hours.
Got a good spot in the middle of the field and the band did not disappoint. Very well played show with an exceptional post drums.
Woke up hungover the next morning and my buddy drove us to OK City for Jerry’s 40th birthday. Those were the days my friends!
